{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "At present, generative models have shown great potential in many application fields [1].",
    "However, traditional generative language models mainly rely on a large amount of pre-trained data for learning.",
    "Although these models can generate relatively coherent text, their generation ability is still limited when facing external knowledge or complex background information.",
    "To this end, the retrieval-augmented generation model (RAG) came into being.",
    "By combining the retrieval system with the generation model, it can dynamically access external knowledge during the generation process, thereby greatly improving the quality and accuracy of generation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "At present, generative models have shown great potential in many application fields [1]."
  ]
}